====Adverb====
{{en-adv|-}}

# {{lb|en|slang|chiefly|Northern California}} {{n-g|Intensifier (modifies verbs); to a large extent;}} [[totally]]; [[very much]].
#: ''Dude, I '''helluv''' want to go to the show with you, but I'm soooo grounded.''
#* {{quote-text|year=2002|author=Peggy Vincent|title=Baby Catcher: Chronicles of a Modern Midwife|page=225|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=LHlQxW68nfYC&pg=PA225&dq=helluv&lr=&sig=bwXyIRbEAOtYNvTzUQjVRZI7_zA|passage=“[…]. This '''helluv''' hurts.” We grownups burst out laughing, and I hugged her bony adolescent shoulders.}}
# {{lb|en|slang|chiefly|Northern California}} {{n-g|Intensifier (modifies adjectives);}} to a large degree; [[extremely]]; [[exceedingly]].
#: ''That new girl is '''helluv''' sexy.''
#* {{quote-text|year=2002|author=Peggy Vincent|title=Baby Catcher: Chronicles of a Modern Midwife|page=226|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=LHlQxW68nfYC&pg=PA226&dq=helluv&lr=&sig=ZjN3r5TaSnTBqIcXNcXxNRQq_PA|passage=“We had the baby, like two minutes ago. It was '''helluv''' icy. […] Naeema was so brave, just hellabitchin', and I delivered the baby myself 'cause we have this hellafresh midwife who taught me how to do it.”}}
#* {{quote-text|year=2003|author=Adrienne Anderson|title=Word: Rap, Politics and Feminism|page=14|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=j3kx-pqoSewC&pg=PA14&dq=helluv&lr=&sig=lSfUATVjJW2QQl2zRn0nwOZ-sBc|passage=“Man, if I had never been to California and read that magazine, I would be '''helluv''' scared to come out there!”}}

